    "ideation": "The Nine-Thirty clock represents mechanical time, rhythmic ticking, and the sudden tension of an approaching deadline. Instead of a literal clock, the performance treats the face as the inner clockwork. The eyes become the hands, initially set at the 9:30 positions (left and down), while the mouth acts as the oscillating balance spring. The animation arc moves from a steady, clinical 'tick-tock' into a high-speed mechanical blur as the gear train 'unwinds,' concluding with the chime of the hour. Color shifts from cold industrial steel to a golden brass resonance.",
